 <div>
<div class="commentcontent">
<p>Hi, I noticed that Secrets does not ask for the admin password during installation. A standard or network user is allowed to install secrets without typing in any password. This is very nasty in a company where the users all are network users on a server with only standard rights. They are not allowed to install or update anything, just to not mix up anything. But they are able to install Secrets even for all users on a machine, because Secrets does not ask for a password. This is definitively not wanted. </p><p>HOW CAN I PREVENT STANDARD OR NETWORK USERS FROM INSTALLING SECRETS??? </p>
</div>
 
 
